products and services.

00:12:06.450 --> 00:12:08.510
The original example
is Sunkist Oranges.

00:12:08.510 --> 00:12:11.440
There was a surplus of
fruit, perishable product.

00:12:11.440 --> 00:12:13.522
California marketers
said, can you help us?

00:12:13.522 --> 00:12:14.980
We don't know what
to do with this.

00:12:14.980 --> 00:12:16.520
We're going to lose a fortune.

00:12:16.520 --> 00:12:19.240
Ad team came together and
said, let's talk about orange

00:12:19.240 --> 00:12:20.350
juice for breakfast.

00:12:20.350 --> 00:12:22.750
Fast forward 100 years,
orange juice for breakfast

00:12:22.750 --> 00:12:25.060
is a very common thing.

00:12:25.060 --> 00:12:26.700
Little did you know
that that was an ad

00:12:26.700 --> 00:12:28.180
guy that got you into that.

00:12:28.180 --> 00:12:28.860
Same for bacon.

00:12:28.860 --> 00:12:29.970
Same for coffee.

00:12:29.970 --> 00:12:33.310
A lot of the habits
that we currently enjoy

00:12:33.310 --> 00:12:35.390
came from an
advertising guy's idea.

00:12:35.390 --> 00:12:36.870
This might be appropriate.

00:12:36.870 --> 00:12:38.250
