00:23:22.340 --> 00:23:23.556
More lately, huh, Kathleen?

00:23:26.220 --> 00:23:26.950
And here we are.

00:23:26.950 --> 00:23:29.310
So they've expanded the
repertoire to include women.

00:23:29.310 --> 00:23:32.840
So we have Jude Law
having a scotch moment,

00:23:32.840 --> 00:23:36.260
enjoying a moment of success,
perhaps just finishing a film.

00:23:36.260 --> 00:23:39.470
And then we women
playing superhero.

00:23:39.470 --> 00:23:41.282
I mean, why?

00:23:41.282 --> 00:23:43.360
Why can't we have
a successful moment

00:23:43.360 --> 00:23:46.430
that looks more appropriate
and more relaxed and more

00:23:46.430 --> 00:23:47.610
like a scotch moment?

00:23:47.610 --> 00:23:49.850
Understand when I
drink scotch, it's

00:23:49.850 --> 00:23:52.120
not when I put my cape
on and do Wonder Woman.

00:23:55.560 --> 00:23:57.170
The redeeming
feature for Diageo,

00:23:57.170 --> 00:23:59.510
and I will give them this,
this is important to me

00:23:59.510 --> 00:24:00.730
because-- you can't see that.

00:24:00.730 --> 00:24:01.896
It may be in the small type.

00:24:01.896 --> 00:24:04.790
But when Diageo first began
the unisex brand project,

00:24:04.790 --> 00:24:06.480
there were no
women on the board.

00:24:06.480 --> 00:24:10.100
Now five of its 11
directors are women.

00:24:10.100 --> 00:24:11.140
I'm happy about that.

00:24:11.140 --> 00:24:13.570
It's not easy, this game
that we're in, advertising.

00:24:13.570 --> 00:24:15.010
We don't always get it right.

00:24:15.010 --> 00:24:15.900
That's right.

00:24:15.900 --> 00:24:16.954
That's a good outcome.

00:24:16.954 --> 00:24:17.870
They'll get it better.

00:24:17.870 --> 00:24:19.590
I trust they will.

00:24:19.590 --> 00:24:20.222
Technology.

00:24:20.222 --> 00:24:22.430
You would think these
leading-edge guys, particularly

00:24:22.430 --> 00:24:25.430
Apple, would be we're so
forefront, we're so young,

00:24:25.430 --> 00:24:26.620
we'll know all this.

00:24:26.620 --> 00:24:30.560
Just last year they could have
had a really wonderful moment

00:24:30.560 --> 00:24:32.870
for women, but
instead they launched

00:24:32.870 --> 00:24:34.631
a new phone that's pink.

00:24:34.631 --> 00:24:35.380
It's a nice phone.

00:24:35.380 --> 00:24:36.990
I can forgive them for that.

00:24:36.990 --> 00:24:39.280
The worst was their
new app, though,

00:24:39.280 --> 00:24:40.890
that can adjust photography.

00:24:40.890 --> 00:24:43.070
And they demonstrated
it on a woman.

00:24:43.070 --> 00:24:46.280
And they said, look what this
does for resting bitch face.

00:24:46.280 --> 00:24:49.100
And they did the
app that went up.

00:24:49.100 --> 00:24:50.770
Stop laughing so hard.

00:24:53.610 --> 00:24:56.350
So they showed this app
that made her smile.

00:24:56.350 --> 00:24:59.600
So see, you can correct even
a woman who doesn't smile.

00:24:59.600 --> 00:25:03.760
Stop telling us to smile
and just let us be.

00:25:03.760 --> 00:25:05.670
I was disappointed in Apple.

00:25:05.670 --> 00:25:06.380
Fitness.

00:25:06.380 --> 00:25:08.470
More progressive,
much more progressive.

00:25:08.470 --> 00:25:10.740
I have to introduce this
idea here now because it's

00:25:10.740 --> 00:25:11.950
the adoption curve.

00:25:11.950 --> 00:25:14.180
If you talk in advertising
about an idea that's

00:25:14.180 --> 00:25:18.000
before its time, innovators and
early adopters, it will fail.

00:25:18.000 --> 00:25:19.540
It will not get
into the mainstream.

00:25:19.540 --> 00:25:20.950
You will get a tipping point.

00:25:20.950 --> 00:25:22.590
So movies can do this.

00:25:22.590 --> 00:25:24.766
Movies can be in the
innovators and early adopters

00:25:24.766 --> 00:25:26.140
and get infiltrated
into culture.

00:25:26.140 --> 00:25:26.740
We can't.

00:25:26.740 --> 00:25:29.940
We got to cross the chasm
and get into early adopters.

00:25:29.940 --> 00:25:33.600
I want to show you an example
of an ad from the early days

00:25:33.600 --> 00:25:35.850
that I think is really
a shame it was too soon.

00:25:35.850 --> 00:25:36.330
-If you let me play--

00:25:36.330 --> 00:25:37.260
-If you let me play sports--

00:25:37.260 --> 00:25:38.500
-I would like myself more.

00:25:38.500 --> 00:25:39.960
-I would have more
self-confidence.

00:25:39.960 --> 00:25:41.270
-If you let me play sports.

00:25:41.270 --> 00:25:42.110
-If you let me play.

00:25:42.110 --> 00:25:43.120
-If you let me play.

00:25:43.120 --> 00:25:46.430
-I will be 60% less likely
to get breast cancer.

00:25:46.430 --> 00:25:47.780
-I will suffer less depression.

00:25:47.780 --> 00:25:49.190
-If you let me play sports.

00:25:49.190 --> 00:25:52.137
-I will be more likely to
leave a man who beats me.

00:25:52.137 --> 00:25:52.970
-If you let me play.

00:25:52.970 --> 00:25:55.480
-I'll be less likely to get
pregnant before I want to.

00:25:55.480 --> 00:25:56.090
-I will learn.

00:25:56.090 --> 00:25:57.720
-I will learn what it
means to be strong.

00:25:57.720 --> 00:25:58.340
-To be strong.

00:25:58.340 --> 00:25:59.090
-If you let me play.

00:25:59.090 --> 00:25:59.650
-Play sports.

00:25:59.650 --> 00:26:01.424
-If you let me play sports.

00:26:05.300 --> 00:26:09.070
-That ad changed the
trajectory of my career.

00:26:09.070 --> 00:26:12.245
When I saw that, I knew what
I wanted to do in advertising.

00:26:12.245 --> 00:26:14.840
It wasn't just to sell
toothpaste and life insurance

00:26:14.840 --> 00:26:15.900
and alcoholic beverages.

00:26:15.900 --> 00:26:17.550
I wanted to change the world.

00:26:17.550 --> 00:26:19.450
I loved it.

00:26:19.450 --> 00:26:20.370
And I was so excited.

00:26:20.370 --> 00:26:22.530
And it was 1995.

00:26:22.530 --> 00:26:24.570
And it just, mmm.

00:26:24.570 --> 00:26:27.630
I mean, there were facts,
medical, scientific facts

00:26:27.630 --> 00:26:30.020
that proved why it's better
to let women play sports.

00:26:30.020 --> 00:26:31.600
It was too soon.

00:26:31.600 --> 00:26:32.840
It was just too soon.

00:26:32.840 --> 00:26:35.280
So happily, Nike
picked up the pace

00:26:35.280 --> 00:26:37.694
and now they're doing
work for Under Armour

00:26:37.694 --> 00:26:39.610
and there are a number
of other fitness brands

00:26:39.610 --> 00:26:41.220
are doing magnificent work.

00:26:41.220 --> 00:26:42.870
But it was just too soon.

00:26:42.870 --> 00:26:45.080
So that's why the timing
for us is very important.

00:26:45.080 --> 00:26:46.100
Always, "Like a girl."

00:26:46.100 --> 00:26:47.310
I think you're
familiar with this.

00:26:47.310 --> 00:26:48.101
A very simple idea.

00:26:48.101 --> 00:26:51.330
-Show me what it looks
like to run like a girl.

00:26:51.330 --> 00:26:52.326
-Oh, my hair.

00:26:52.326 --> 00:26:53.820
Oh my god.

00:26:53.820 --> 00:26:56.712
-Show me what it looks
like to fight like a girl.

00:26:56.712 --> 00:26:57.945
-Throw like a girl.

00:27:01.590 --> 00:27:03.640
-Show me what it looks
like to run like a girl.

00:27:07.390 --> 00:27:09.490
-Throw like a girl.

00:27:09.490 --> 00:27:12.387
What does it mean to you
when I say "run like a girl"?

00:27:12.387 --> 00:27:14.610
-It means run fast as you can.

00:27:18.580 --> 00:27:21.420
-Such a simple idea and such a
wonderful, wonderful campaign.

00:27:21.420 --> 00:27:24.090
And you'll notice that
there's no product in there,

00:27:24.090 --> 00:27:26.750
but it did extraordinary
things for P&amp;G and for Always

00:27:26.750 --> 00:27:30.010
because people are wanting to
know what do you stand for?

00:27:30.010 --> 00:27:31.204
Why are you on this planet?

00:27:31.204 --> 00:27:33.120
It's not just to sell
me stuff, but you better

00:27:33.120 --> 00:27:35.240
stand for something
that's important to me.

00:27:35.240 --> 00:27:36.290
Brilliant job.

00:27:36.290 --> 00:27:38.180
Absolutely brilliant
job for them.

00:27:38.180 --> 00:27:39.720
UK-- "This Girl Can."

00:27:39.720 --> 00:27:41.070
Some wonderful images.

00:27:41.070 --> 00:27:42.730
"I don't swim because
I hate my body.

00:27:42.730 --> 00:27:44.330
It's because I love my body."

00:27:44.330 --> 00:27:46.530
Really wonderful work
around the world.

00:27:46.530 --> 00:27:47.140
Fashion.

00:27:47.140 --> 00:27:48.840
Last but not least,
fashion you can

00:27:48.840 --> 00:27:51.295
expect to be at the
forefront because they really

00:27:51.295 --> 00:27:52.170
are the leading edge.

00:27:52.170 --> 00:27:54.312
They don't have to appeal
to the mainstream--

00:27:54.312 --> 00:27:56.770
that grid that I showed you--
like the rest of our products

00:27:56.770 --> 00:27:57.300
do.

00:27:57.300 --> 00:27:59.150
They can be a
little leading edge,

00:27:59.150 --> 00:28:00.652
and then it trickles through.

00:28:00.652 --> 00:28:01.860
Look at this wonderful thing.

00:28:01.860 --> 00:28:02.360
I'm on it.

00:28:02.360 --> 00:28:03.660
Thank you.

00:28:03.660 --> 00:28:06.040
That's Jaden Smith
on the other side.

00:28:06.040 --> 00:28:07.390
I just love this ad.

00:28:07.390 --> 00:28:08.270
It's just delightful.

00:28:08.270 --> 00:28:09.630
He's wearing a skirt.

00:28:09.630 --> 00:28:10.320
Happy as a clam.

00:28:10.320 --> 00:28:11.220
He looks fabulous.

00:28:11.220 --> 00:28:12.210
He looks really cool.

00:28:12.210 --> 00:28:17.060
He's not saying anything other
than I love wearing this.

00:28:17.060 --> 00:28:19.524
Whether gender is identity
or gender is performance,

00:28:19.524 --> 00:28:21.940
this is an absolutely delightful
way of looking at things,

00:28:21.940 --> 00:28:24.450
and going, cool.

00:28:24.450 --> 00:28:27.050
And last but not least,
this is an example to me

00:28:27.050 --> 00:28:28.800
of gender fluidity
in advertising.

00:28:28.800 --> 00:28:31.070
It's from Asia.

00:28:31.070 --> 00:28:32.708
Sorry, Old Spice.

00:28:32.708 --> 00:28:34.700
I forgot about this one.

00:28:34.700 --> 00:28:37.660
This is from another
planet altogether.

00:28:37.660 --> 00:28:39.960
Old Spice did some work
where they objectified

00:28:39.960 --> 00:28:43.300
men the way women used to be
objectified in Budweiser ads,

00:28:43.300 --> 00:28:44.320
but they made it funny.

00:28:44.320 --> 00:28:45.660
They took the sting out of it.

00:28:45.660 --> 00:28:46.970
I still have some questions.

00:28:46.970 --> 00:28:51.194
If you had a woman put in the
same position where they said,

00:28:51.194 --> 00:28:52.860
look at your girlfriend,
now look at me.

00:28:52.860 --> 00:28:54.310
Look at your girlfriend,
now look at me,

00:28:54.310 --> 00:28:55.380
we would be very upset.

00:28:55.380 --> 00:28:57.727
But they did it with
guys, and it was funny.

00:28:57.727 --> 00:28:59.060
And it took the sting out of it.

00:28:59.060 --> 00:29:01.337
The jury's still
out on that one.

00:29:01.337 --> 00:29:03.170
Last but not least,
look at this from Japan.

00:29:13.750 --> 00:31:24.530
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:31:24.530 --> 00:31:26.730
So many extraordinary
metaphors in that.

00:31:26.730 --> 00:31:29.450
The tag line in the
end there, given

00:31:29.450 --> 00:31:31.550
I think is a very
powerful story line

00:31:31.550 --> 00:31:34.366
is, makeup can make
anybody look cute.

00:31:37.950 --> 00:31:40.250
Male, female, who cares?

00:31:40.250 --> 00:31:44.200
Just an absolutely
delightful piece of work.

00:31:44.200 --> 00:31:46.160
What we want-- listen.

00:31:46.160 --> 00:31:47.860
Ask the right
questions, but listen.

00:31:47.860 --> 00:31:49.110
I mean, really listen.

00:31:49.110 --> 00:31:49.974
Get to know people.

00:31:49.974 --> 00:31:51.640
The way we do better
work is to actually

00:31:51.640 --> 00:31:52.730
talk to them one on one.

00:31:52.730 --> 00:31:54.170
We call it exploring.

00:31:54.170 --> 00:31:55.380
We live with them.

00:31:55.380 --> 00:31:58.030
What's important to them,
what do they care about.

00:31:58.030 --> 00:32:01.190
It's absolutely critical for us.

00:32:01.190 --> 00:32:04.440
We get on to the data at one
point, but we've got to listen.

00:32:04.440 --> 00:32:07.250
And that means
close up one on one.

00:32:07.250 --> 00:32:08.100
Be authentic.

00:32:08.100 --> 00:32:09.510
Understand the experience.

00:32:09.510 --> 00:32:11.470
What is the scotch
drinking experience?

00:32:11.470 --> 00:32:13.140
What is the beer
drinking experience?

00:32:13.140 --> 00:32:15.679
Don't just put a woman
slapped on it and think,

00:32:15.679 --> 00:32:17.720
well, she might like this
because she likes pink.

00:32:17.720 --> 00:32:19.690
I mean, that's so old.

00:32:19.690 --> 00:32:23.850
And finally, target the
experience, not the gender.

00:32:23.850 --> 00:32:25.600
We are so over targeting gender.

00:32:25.600 --> 00:32:27.014
It's just not even appropriate.

00:32:27.014 --> 00:32:27.680
It doesn't work.

00:32:27.680 --> 00:32:30.210
And happily, the younger
guys coming up-- god

00:32:30.210 --> 00:32:33.180
bless our millennials--
they want far more equality

00:32:33.180 --> 00:32:34.280
between men and women.

00:32:34.280 --> 00:32:36.020
So I think the future is bright.

00:32:36.020 --> 00:32:36.743
Thank you.

